From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chengfeng Lin <lin2530632123@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [RFC CANDIDATE] mm/mprotect: avoid shared folio lookup without a
 batch hint

The PTE path currently calls vm_normal_page() before it knows whether
folio-based PTE batching can help.  On architectures whose
pte_batch_hint() returns one, this adds a vmemmap lookup to every ordinary
PTE even though a shared mapping does not need struct page information for
the writable decision.

Avoid the lookup for non-NUMA shared mappings when the architecture cannot
offer a batch larger than one from the PTE alone.  Private writable mappings
still perform the lookup for anonymous exclusivity, NUMA protection still
performs it for folio eligibility, and architectures with a larger PTE batch
hint retain folio batching.

This is an experimental performance candidate, not a proposed upstream fix.
In particular, pte_batch_hint() returns one on x86 even for a PTE-mapped
large folio, so this trades away folio batching for that shared mapping shape.
The accompanying experiment therefore includes a mandatory PTE-mapped large
folio reverse check.

Signed-off-by: Chengfeng Lin <lin2530632123@gmail.com>
---
 mm/mprotect.c | 38 ++++++++++++++++++++++----------------
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+), 16 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/mprotect.c b/mm/mprotect.c
index b581c4c02f01..7ee2a5bdd9ee 100644
--- a/mm/mprotect.c
+++ b/mm/mprotect.c
@@ -344,6 +344,6 @@ static long change_pte_range(struct mmu_gather *tlb,
 			int max_nr_ptes = (end - addr) >> PAGE_SHIFT;
 			struct folio *folio = NULL;
-			struct page *page;
+			struct page *page = NULL;
 
 			/* Already in the desired state. */
 			if (prot_numa && pte_protnone(oldpte))
@@ -352,23 +352,29 @@ static long change_pte_range(struct mmu_gather *tlb,
 
-			page = vm_normal_page(vma, addr, oldpte);
-			if (page)
-				folio = page_folio(page);
+			if (likely(!prot_numa && (vma->vm_flags & VM_SHARED) &&
+				   pte_batch_hint(pte, oldpte) == 1)) {
+				nr_ptes = 1;
+			} else {
+				page = vm_normal_page(vma, addr, oldpte);
+				if (page)
+					folio = page_folio(page);
 
-			/*
-			 * Avoid trapping faults against the zero or KSM
-			 * pages. See similar comment in change_huge_pmd.
-			 */
-			if (prot_numa &&
-			    !folio_can_map_prot_numa(folio, vma,
-						is_private_single_threaded)) {
+				/*
+				 * Avoid trapping faults against the zero or KSM
+				 * pages. See similar comment in change_huge_pmd.
+				 */
+				if (prot_numa &&
+				    !folio_can_map_prot_numa(folio, vma,
+							is_private_single_threaded)) {
 
-				/* determine batch to skip */
-				nr_ptes = mprotect_folio_pte_batch(folio,
-					  pte, oldpte, max_nr_ptes, /* flags = */ 0);
-				continue;
-			}
+					/* determine batch to skip */
+					nr_ptes = mprotect_folio_pte_batch(folio,
+						  pte, oldpte, max_nr_ptes, /* flags = */ 0);
+					continue;
+				}
 
-			nr_ptes = mprotect_folio_pte_batch(folio, pte, oldpte, max_nr_ptes, flags);
+				nr_ptes = mprotect_folio_pte_batch(folio, pte,
+						oldpte, max_nr_ptes, flags);
+			}
 
 			/*
 			 * Optimize for the small-folio common case by
